## MIXA-027: COST Module — Complete

**Task**: Implement COST module in Go engine (MIXA-027)

**What was built** (`engine/internal/modules/cost/`):
- **COST module** with full Fenix UI protocol integration
- **Provider adapters**: ManualAdapter, DigitalOceanAdapter, AWSAdapter (interface-based, ready for real API integration)
- **Provider configuration**: API key management, enable/disable per provider
- **Cost polling**: configurable schedule (hourly/daily) with background goroutine
- **Cost data**: time-series entries stored in encrypted SQLite (AES-256-GCM)
- **Budget system**: per-scope budgets (total, provider:X, project:X) with 80%/90%/100% threshold alerts
- **UIView**: MetricRow (monthly spend, projected, budget, entries), area Chart (30-day daily costs), Table (per-service breakdown), Form (add entry), budget alerts
- **Actions**: Add Entry, Delete Entry, Set Budget, Delete Budget, Export CSV, Configure Provider, Set Schedule, View History, Refresh
- **Export CSV**: full cost history export
- **40 tests**: all passing, covering cost calculations, budget thresholds, persistence, UI view, event handling, subscriber pattern

**Backpressure checks**: All pass (go vet, go test, go build, pnpm typecheck, lint, test, build)

**Commits**: `0794203` (initial implementation) + `eccdeb9` (provider adapters and polling)

